cs.MA, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a payment mechanism to incentivize high-effort sensing from workers in mobile crowd sensing systems. The paper focuses on game theory and mechanism design to address workers' strategic behavior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a truth discovery algorithm based on quality-aware data aggregation. The paper also discusses the non-cooperative game induced by the payment mechanism, which suggests cs.GT (Game Theory) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses simulations to validate the proposed mechanism, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
